Hoy dejemos el horror de lado. Hablemos de Zelda. Mejor, hablemos de Link.

The Legend of Zelda: Link's Awakening (2019, Nintendo Switch) es un videojuego de acción y aventura que a su vez es un remake del videojuego del mismo nombre editado para la GameBoy en 1993.

Como todas las entregas de la veterana franquicia de la Gran N, este Zelda es un juego en el que predomina la aventura, la estética muy cuidada y las sensaciones de jugador más allá de todo lo demás.

Entretenido, divertido... y muy bonito. Casi parece que estemos jugando en un diorama con nuestros juguetes del a infancia.

Fácil y asequible (hasta que intentemos pasarlo en modo héroe, chavales!). #nintendo #nintendoswitch #switch #zelda #legendofzelda #linksawakeningremake #linksawakening #gameboy #remake #secuela #saga #horrorelhorror #fangofan

caption.text:
Do you know how to fight !? Tekken is a huge series in the gaming world, but Tekken 3 is beloved as the peak of the series. You get a lot in this game of modes to play that keeps it fun. There is your typical arcade , V.S. , tag team modes.Tekken Force is a weird adventure mode that you can play to see how fast you can go through enemies in a side scroller. This game got over 20 plus character to keep it fun. I think people just like Gon the the orange baby t-Rex who is really hard to fight against. Personally being kicked around by a panda bear or a wooden doll with ball chain hands is more insulting to be beat by. The story is weird with 
Heihachi trying to resurrect an aztec ogre for power and everyone trying to stop both. So kinda like an episode of Jojo’s bizarre adventure. The combat is still pretty spot on for 1998 which I think is why most people hold this game is held high. That or nostalgia from playing in the arcades with friends and strangers. 7.5/10 #arcade #tekken #tekken3 #namco #nintendoswitch #nintendo #ps1 #playstation #playstationclassic #oldschool #retro #xbox #xbox360 #xboxlive #xboxone #90s #fight #world #friends #family #pc #pcgaming #steam

Raiders of the Lost Ark is an action-adventure game created for the Atari 2600 based on the movie of the same name (the first installment of the Indiana Jones series). The game was designed by Howard Scott Warshaw.

The player controls Indiana Jones as he searches for the lost Ark of the Covenant. The game requires the player to use two different controllers: controller 2 moves Jones and its button uses an item; controller 1 selects the item to use and its button drops the item. This control scheme anticipated later game controllers with more buttons and games where buttons would allow the player to switch items without interrupting gameplay. (Source @wikipedia)

"Gun Gun Pixies è un’esperienza che diverte per la sua leggerezza e fanservice. Non portando nulla di nuovo all’interno del settore più ecchi, si limita a elaborare la sua idea e a completarla il meglio possibile, utilizzando come maggior punti di forza un’art direction ben studiata e un ritmo di gameplay semplice ma efficace. Purtroppo la mancanza di uno vero spessore narrativo, un level design scomodo e una certa ripetitività evidente lo rendono un prodotto mirato quasi esclusivamente all’imperdibile appassionato della filosofia osé di PQube e Idea Factory/Compile Heart, perdendo l’occasione di poter sfruttare al meglio l’originalità dell’idea di base."La mia recensione per Tom's Hardware Game Division!⠀

preview_comments.text: Das ist ja cool in welche Richtung geht es da mit der Strategie ? Tatsächlich liebe ich klassisches Mensch ärgere dich nicht und monopoly ( mit meinen Schwestern und dann eskaliert es immer 😂👌🏻) aber derzeit spiele ich Supergerne auch die Black Storys . Kann ich echt nur empfehlen !

@apfelmotte_gaming Monopoly ist mein absolutes Hassspiel. Da eskaliert IMMER die Stimmung ab einem gewissen Punkt. 😂 Man spielt in zwei Teams, muss als Team überlegen wie man vorgeht oder Züge bündeln kann. Da kommen echt immer lustige Diskussionen zustande, wer sich auch mal opfert usw. 😂 Und Black Stories finde ich in größeren Runden auch schön. 😊

caption.text:
》Guten Morgen ihr Gamerchen《
So schnell geht es, da ist schon #Bergfest . 😂
Die liebe @apfelmotte_gaming hatte in ihrem aktuellen Post gefragt, was wir noch für Hobbies neben Videospielen haben und da wollte ich euch auch dran teilhaben lassen.
Denn Brett- und Gemeinschaftsspiele sind auch ein großer Teil unseres Lebens.
Dieses WOW Brettspiel gibt es leider nur noch gebraucht und wir freuten uns riesig, als wir es noch für unter 100€ ergattern konnten.
Es ist wirklich abendfüllend und bedarf einiger Strategie. Aber es macht riesigen Spaß!
Spielt ihr auch gerne Gemeinschaftsspiele und wenn ja, welche sind eure liebsten?
.
》Which boardgame is your favourite?《
.

.

横浜カップが無事に終わりました。
今回も入賞出来ませんでした。
またあと一歩足りず…
試合は、勝ちか負けしかありません。
メンタルがガラスの様な息子な為、試合は、下がるスタイル笑
歳を重ねるごとに試合に対して弱気、緊張が増してしまい、いつもの稽古の動きが全く出来ない。
あまりにもずーっと情けない試合ばかりで、励ます言葉も出ない試合ばかりでした。
なのでjosoからゲーム禁止令を出していたのですが、横浜カップでは、負けてしまいましたが、少しガラスからプラスチック位に成長していたので、自信⁉️試合が少しでも発表の場として楽しむ⁉️やってやる‼️って思ってくれればとゲームを少しだけ解禁してみました。

少しだけです笑

一日、Fortniteを死ぬのが2回まで笑

死ななければ長く出来る
けれど責めないと殺される。

試合と同じです。

しかし、うちの息子は、戦わないで待つタイプらしいです。

#dragonquestxiechidiuneraperduta  #dragonquest #nintendo #nintendoswitch #demo #squareenix #recensione #parliamone 
Dragon Quest XI era uno dei giochi che più mi incuriosivano in questa stagione. Ammetto però che dopo ore giocate alla demo il mio interesse è lentamente scemato. Parliamo dei grandi punti di forza. Dragon Quest dal punto di vista estetico è bellissimo. Colorato, disegni che come sempre ammiccano alla serie di Dragon Ball e con una colonna sonora magistralmente diretta. Anche se sulla Switch in versione portatile perde molto, anzi sembra quasi che i luoghi più luminosi sembrano sgranati. Ma a mio avviso il problema principale è in gioco. I poligoni sono molto belli da vedere ma si muovono e interagiscono tra loro in un modo che non si vedeva da giochi della PS2. Il sistema di combattimento non è chissà quanto rivoluzionario e a volte risulta confuso e molto lento. Dalla demo non si ha modo di esplorare a pieno però tutto il compartimento GDR. In fine la trama sembra essere davvero molto avvincente ma agli inizi sembra troppo frettolosa sembrando a volte poco naturale. Spero che i difetti notati siano legati solo alla demo. Ma per i fan della saga forse può risultare un titolo imperdibile.

I didn’t actually sit down and play it myself until a few years back, and I’m so so glad I did 💖 I’m planning on eventually getting the remaster, but until then I’ll just be playing through the original :P
I also may or may not be planning on redrawing one of my favorite pieces I’ve ever done regarding this game very soon 🤫
Also if you’re wondering where this came from, and don’t feel like going back one post, the original doodle from my algebra notes is on the next slide.

Short Story :
.
Shin sat in the tall grass, on the hunt for a Meowth. These creatures were not that easy to catch. They were fast. And their Eevee was not fast enough to go after them.
Eevee was tired of running around so they decided to take a break next to the river that flows along Cerulean City.
"You're not strong enough, Aberdeen" the trainer talks to its pokemon. "How are we going to win against the dangerous pokemon in that cave?" They point upstream. There was a dangerous cave over there known for their ferocious pokemon.
Aberdeen looked up at Shin with a firm look. The Eevee let out a scream of determination. Right at that moment, something jumps out of the water! A squirtle!
"I believe in you, Aberdeen. You are going to be strong! Now, this is your next opponent!"
And before the squirtle realized it, the trainer caught it inside of a pokeball.
